     1→# Widget Development Guide
     2→
     3→**Last Updated:** November 19, 2025
     4→**Status:** ✅ Active
     5→**Source:** Validated from codebase audit + Gemini analysis
     6→
     7→---
     8→
     9→## Overview
    10→
    11→The Neuman Brain Dashboard features a modular widget system with 49+ widgets across 7 categories. This guide provides the complete specification for creating, registering, and deploying new dashboard widgets.
    12→
    13→## Widget System Architecture
    14→
    15→**Location:** `src/widgets/Dashboard/`
    16→
    17→**Core Components:**
    18→- **`BaseWidget.tsx`** - Reusable wrapper providing loading states, error handling, refresh buttons, and consistent styling
    19→- **`WidgetRegistry.ts`** - Central registry mapping widget IDs to metadata, API configuration, and categories
    20→- **Individual widget files** - Self-contained React components (e.g., `QuoteWidget.tsx`, `CryptoWidget.tsx`)
    21→
    22→**Current Widget Count (Nov 2025):** 49 widgets
    23→- **Core:** 2 widgets (Upcoming Events, Recent Notes)
    24→- **Productivity:** 7 widgets (Quote, Pomodoro, Word of Day, Currency, World Clock, etc.)
    25→- **News:** 7 widgets (Hacker News, Reddit, Dev.to, AI Research, Wikipedia, etc.)
    26→- **Finance:** 3 widgets (Crypto, Stock Market)
    27→- **Fun:** 5 widgets (Jokes, Facts, Bored, Memory Game, Typing Test)
    28→- **Visual:** 1 widget (Weather Map)
    29→- **Dev:** 8 widgets (GitHub, NPM Stats, GitHub Trending, Repo Stats, etc.)
    30→- **Utility:** 16 widgets (IP Info, QR Code, Calculator, Unit Converter, Clipboard, etc.)
    31→
    32→---
    33→
    34→## Creating a Widget: Step-by-Step Guide
    35→
    36→### Step 1: Create the Widget Component
    37→
    38→Create a new file: `src/widgets/Dashboard/[WidgetName]Widget.tsx`
    39→
    40→**Minimal Widget Template:**
    41→```typescript
    42→/**
    43→ * [Widget Name] Widget
    44→ *
    45→ * [Brief description of what this widget does]
    46→ */
    47→
    48→import React, { useState, useEffect, useCallback } from 'react';
    49→import { BaseWidget } from './BaseWidget';
    50→
    51→export const MyNewWidget: React.FC = () => {
    52→  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true);
    53→  const [error, setError] = useState<string | null>(null);
    54→
    55→  const fetchData = useCallback(async () => {
    56→    setLoading(true);
    57→    setError(null);
    58→
    59→    try {
    60→      // Your data fetching logic here
    61→      setLoading(false);
    62→    } catch (err) {
    63→      setError(err instanceof Error ? err.message : 'Failed to load data');
    64→      setLoading(false);
    65→    }
    66→  }, []);
    67→
    68→  // Initial fetch
    69→  useEffect(() => {
    70→    fetchData();
    71→  }, [fetchData]);
    72→
    73→  return (
    74→    <BaseWidget
    75→      title="My Widget"
    76→      icon="⚡"
    77→      loading={loading}
    78→      error={error}
    79→      onRefresh={fetchData}
    80→    >
    81→      {/* Your widget content here */}
    82→      <div className="flex flex-col gap-2">
    83→        <p className="text-text-light-primary dark:text-text-dark-primary">
    84→          Widget content goes here
    85→        </p>
    86→      </div>
    87→    </BaseWidget>
    88→  );
    89→};
    90→```
    91→
    92→### Step 2: Register the Widget
    93→
    94→Add your widget to `src/widgets/Dashboard/WidgetRegistry.ts`:
    95→
    96→```typescript
    97→// 1. Import the widget component (at top of file)
    98→import { MyNewWidget } from './MyNewWidget';
    99→
   100→// 2. Add to WIDGET_REGISTRY object
   101→export const WIDGET_REGISTRY: Record<string, WidgetDefinition> = {
   102→  // ... existing widgets
   103→
   104→  mynewwidget: {
   105→    id: 'mynewwidget',
   106→    name: 'My New Widget',
   107→    description: 'Brief description for settings UI',
   108→    icon: '⚡',
   109→    category: 'utility', // core | productivity | news | finance | fun | visual | dev | utility
   110→    apiUrl: 'https://api.example.com/endpoint', // Optional - only if using external API
   111→    requiresAuth: false, // Set true if widget needs user configuration (API key, username)
   112→    defaultEnabled: false, // Set true to auto-enable for new users
   113→  },
   114→};
   115→```
   116→
   117→### Step 3: Add to Dashboard Page
   118→
   119→The widget will **automatically appear** in the Dashboard's widget selector once registered. No manual updates needed to `Dashboard.tsx`.
   120→
   121→**How it works:**
   122→- `Dashboard.tsx` reads `WIDGET_REGISTRY` at runtime
   123→- User can enable/disable widgets from Settings
   124→- Widget positions are saved to IndexedDB
   125→
   126→---
   127→
   128→## BaseWidget API Reference
   129→
   130→The `BaseWidget` component provides a consistent wrapper for all dashboard widgets.
   131→
   132→**Props:**
   133→```typescript
   134→interface BaseWidgetProps {
   135→  title: string;           // Widget title (displays in header)
   136→  icon: string;            // Emoji icon (displays next to title)
   137→  children: React.ReactNode; // Widget content
   138→  loading?: boolean;       // Shows loading spinner if true
   139→  error?: string | null;   // Shows error message if not null
   140→  onRefresh?: () => void;  // Refresh button handler (optional)
   141→  onSettings?: () => void; // Settings button handler (optional)
   142→  className?: string;      // Additional CSS classes (optional)
   143→}
   144→```
   145→
   146→**Features Provided by BaseWidget:**
   147→- ✅ **Loading state** - Animated spinner with "Loading..." text
   148→- ✅ **Error handling** - User-friendly error display with retry button
   149→- ✅ **Refresh button** - Automatic refresh UI with spin animation
   150→- ✅ **Settings button** - Optional configuration UI
   151→- ✅ **Dark mode support** - Automatic theme switching
   152→- ✅ **Animations** - Smooth fade-in on mount (Framer Motion)
   153→- ✅ **Consistent styling** - Matches design system (surface colors, text colors, shadows)
   154→
   155→**Example Usage:**
   156→```typescript
   157→<BaseWidget
   158→  title="Weather Forecast"
   159→  icon="🌤️"
   160→  loading={isLoading}
   161→  error={errorMessage}
   162→  onRefresh={fetchWeather}
   163→  onSettings={openSettingsModal}
   164→>
   165→  {/* Your widget content */}
   166→</BaseWidget>
   167→```
   168→
   169→---
   170→
   171→## Widget Examples
   172→
   173→### Example 1: Static Widget (No API)
   174→
   175→**Use case:** Calculator, Pomodoro Timer, Pixel Art
   176→
   177→```typescript
   178→import React, { useState } from 'react';
   179→import { BaseWidget } from './BaseWidget';
   180→
   181→export const CalculatorWidget: React.FC = () => {
   182→  const [result, setResult] = useState<string>('0');
   183→
   184→  const handleButtonClick = (value: string) => {
   185→    // Calculator logic
   186→    setResult(value);
   187→  };
   188→
   189→  return (
   190→    <BaseWidget title="Calculator" icon="🔢">
   191→      <div className="grid grid-cols-4 gap-2 p-2">
   192→        {/* Calculator buttons */}
   193→        <div className="col-span-4 bg-surface-light-elevated dark:bg-surface-dark p-3 rounded text-right text-2xl font-mono">
   194→          {result}
   195→        </div>
   196→        {/* Number buttons... */}
   197→      </div>
   198→    </BaseWidget>
   199→  );
   200→};
   201→```
   202→
   203→### Example 2: Simple API Widget
   204→
   205→**Use case:** Quote of the Day, Random Facts, Crypto Prices
   206→
   207→```typescript
   208→import React, { useState, useEffect, useCallback } from 'react';
   209→import { BaseWidget } from './BaseWidget';
   210→
   211→interface Quote {
   212→  content: string;
   213→  author: string;
   214→}
   215→
   216→export const QuoteWidget: React.FC = () => {
   217→  const [quote, setQuote] = useState<Quote | null>(null);
   218→  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true);
   219→  const [error, setError] = useState<string | null>(null);
   220→
   221→  const fetchQuote = useCallback(async () => {
   222→    setLoading(true);
   223→    setError(null);
   224→
   225→    try {
   226→      const response = await fetch('https://api.quotable.io/random');
   227→      if (!response.ok) throw new Error('Failed to fetch quote');
   228→
   229→      const data = await response.json();
   230→      setQuote({ content: data.content, author: data.author });
   231→    } catch (err) {
   232→      setError(err instanceof Error ? err.message : 'Failed to load quote');
   233→    } finally {
   234→      setLoading(false);
   235→    }
   236→  }, []);
   237→
   238→  useEffect(() => {
   239→    fetchQuote();
   240→  }, [fetchQuote]);
   241→
   242→  return (
   243→    <BaseWidget
   244→      title="Daily Quote"
   245→      icon="💭"
   246→      loading={loading}
   247→      error={error}
   248→      onRefresh={fetchQuote}
   249→    >
   250→      {quote && (
   251→        <div className="flex flex-col gap-4">
   252→          <blockquote className="text-base italic text-text-light-primary dark:text-text-dark-primary">
   253→            "{quote.content}"
   254→          </blockquote>
   255→          <p className="text-sm text-text-light-secondary dark:text-text-dark-secondary text-right">
   256→            — {quote.author}
   257→          </p>
   258→        </div>
   259→      )}
   260→    </BaseWidget>
   261→  );
   262→};
   263→```
   264→
   265→### Example 3: Weather Widget with Open-Meteo API
   266→
   267→**Use case:** Weather Forecast, Air Quality, Location-based data
   268→
   269→```typescript
   270→import React, { useState, useEffect, useCallback } from 'react';
   271→import { BaseWidget } from './BaseWidget';
   272→
   273→interface ForecastDay {
   274→  date: string;
   275→  tempMax: number;
   276→  tempMin: number;
   277→  weatherCode: number;
   278→}
   279→
   280→export const WeatherForecastWidget: React.FC = () => {
   281→  const [forecast, setForecast] = useState<ForecastDay[]>([]);
   282→  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true);
   283→  const [error, setError] = useState<string | null>(null);
   284→
   285→  const fetchForecast = useCallback(async () => {
   286→    setLoading(true);
   287→    setError(null);
   288→
   289→    try {
   290→      // Open-Meteo API (free, no API key needed)
   291→      const response = await fetch(
   292→        'https://api.open-meteo.com/v1/forecast?latitude=40.7128&longitude=-74.0060&daily=temperature_2m_max,temperature_2m_min,weathercode&temperature_unit=fahrenheit&timezone=America/New_York'
   293→      );
   294→      if (!response.ok) throw new Error('Failed to fetch forecast');
   295→
   296→      const data = await response.json();
   297→      const days: ForecastDay[] = data.daily.time.slice(0, 5).map((date: string, i: number) => ({
   298→        date,
   299→        tempMax: Math.round(data.daily.temperature_2m_max[i]),
   300→        tempMin: Math.round(data.daily.temperature_2m_min[i]),
   301→        weatherCode: data.daily.weathercode[i],
   302→      }));
   303→
   304→      setForecast(days);
   305→    } catch (err) {
   306→      setError(err instanceof Error ? err.message : 'Failed to load forecast');
   307→    } finally {
   308→      setLoading(false);
   309→    }
   310→  }, []);
   311→
   312→  useEffect(() => {
   313→    fetchForecast();
   314→  }, [fetchForecast]);
   315→
   316→  const getWeatherIcon = (code: number) => {
   317→    if (code === 0) return '☀️';
   318→    if (code <= 3) return '⛅';
   319→    if (code <= 67) return '🌧️';
   320→    if (code <= 77) return '❄️';
   321→    return '🌤️';
   322→  };
   323→
   324→  const formatDate = (dateStr: string) => {
   325→    const date = new Date(dateStr);
   326→    return date.toLocaleDateString('en-US', { weekday: 'short', month: 'short', day: 'numeric' });
   327→  };
   328→
   329→  return (
   330→    <BaseWidget
   331→      title="Weather Forecast"
   332→      icon="🌤️"
   333→      loading={loading}
   334→      error={error}
   335→      onRefresh={fetchForecast}
   336→    >
   337→      {forecast.length > 0 && (
   338→        <div className="space-y-2">
   339→          {forecast.map((day) => (
   340→            <div
   341→              key={day.date}
   342→              className="flex items-center justify-between p-2 bg-surface-light-elevated dark:bg-surface-dark rounded"
   343→            >
   344→              <span className="text-sm text-text-light-secondary dark:text-text-dark-secondary min-w-[80px]">
   345→                {formatDate(day.date)}
   346→              </span>
   347→              <span className="text-2xl">{getWeatherIcon(day.weatherCode)}</span>
   348→              <div className="flex gap-2 text-sm font-medium text-text-light-primary dark:text-text-dark-primary">
   349→                <span>{day.tempMax}°</span>
   350→                <span className="text-text-light-secondary dark:text-text-dark-secondary">
   351→                  {day.tempMin}°
   352→                </span>
   353→              </div>
   354→            </div>
   355→          ))}
   356→        </div>
   357→      )}
   358→    </BaseWidget>
   359→  );
   360→};
   361→```
   362→
   363→---
   364→
   365→## Styling Guidelines
   366→
   367→### Color System
   368→
   369→**IMPORTANT:** Always use semantic color tokens, never hardcoded colors.
   370→
   371→**Available color tokens:**
   372→```typescript
   373→// Surface colors (backgrounds)
   374→bg-surface-light                    // Light mode widget background
   375→bg-surface-light-elevated           // Light mode elevated elements (cards)
   376→bg-surface-dark                     // Dark mode widget background (#000000)
   377→bg-surface-dark-elevated            // Dark mode elevated elements (#121212)
   378→
   379→// Text colors
   380→text-text-light-primary             // Primary text (light mode)
   381→text-text-light-secondary           // Secondary text (light mode)
   382→text-text-dark-primary              // Primary text (dark mode)
   383→text-text-dark-secondary            // Secondary text (dark mode)
   384→
   385→// Accent colors (buttons, links, highlights)
   386→bg-accent-blue                      // Primary action blue
   387→bg-accent-blue-hover                // Blue hover state
   388→bg-accent-magenta                   // Secondary accent magenta
   389→bg-accent-cyan                      // Tertiary accent cyan
   390→text-accent-blue                    // Blue text
   391→
   392→// Status colors
   393→text-status-error                   // Error red
   394→text-status-success                 // Success green
   395→text-status-warning                 // Warning orange
   396→
   397→// Border colors
   398→border-border-light                 // Light mode borders
   399→border-border-dark                  // Dark mode borders
   400→```
   401→
   402→**Example:**
   403→```typescript
   404→// ✅ CORRECT - Uses semantic tokens
   405→<div className="bg-surface-light-elevated dark:bg-surface-dark rounded p-3">
   406→  <h3 className="text-text-light-primary dark:text-text-dark-primary font-semibold">
   407→    Title
   408→  </h3>
   409→  <p className="text-text-light-secondary dark:text-text-dark-secondary text-sm">
   410→    Description
   411→  </p>
   412→</div>
   413→
   414→// ❌ WRONG - Hardcoded colors
   415→<div className="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800">
   416→  <h3 className="text-black dark:text-white">Title</h3>
   417→</div>
   418→```
   419→
   420→### Responsive Design
   421→
   422→Widgets must adapt to different container sizes (resizable in Dashboard):
   423→
   424→```typescript
   425→// ✅ Use responsive utilities
   426→<div className="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-2">
   427→  {/* Grid adapts to widget width */}
   428→</div>
   429→
   430→// ✅ Use flexbox for flexibility
   431→<div className="flex flex-col gap-2 h-full">
   432→  {/* Content stretches to fill height */}
   433→</div>
   434→
   435→// ✅ Use w-full and h-full
   436→<div className="w-full h-full overflow-auto">
   437→  {/* Widget fills available space */}
   438→</div>
   439→```
   440→
   441→### Accessibility
   442→
   443→All widgets must meet WCAG AA standards:
   444→
   445→```typescript
   446→// ✅ Use semantic HTML
   447→<button onClick={handleClick}>Click me</button> // Not <div onClick>
   448→
   449→// ✅ Add ARIA labels
   450→<button aria-label="Refresh weather data" onClick={refresh}>
   451→  🔄
   452→</button>
   453→
   454→// ✅ Keyboard navigation
   455→<input
   456→  onKeyDown={(e) => e.key === 'Enter' && handleSubmit()}
   457→  aria-label="Search query"
   458→/>
   459→
   460→// ✅ Focus states
   461→<button className="focus:ring-2 focus:ring-accent-blue">
   462→  Submit
   463→</button>
   464→```
   465→
   466→---
   467→
   468→## Data Handling & State Management
   469→
   470→### Local State (useState)
   471→
   472→Use for widget-specific UI state:
   473→
   474→```typescript
   475→const [selectedTab, setSelectedTab] = useState<'overview' | 'details'>('overview');
   476→const [isExpanded, setIsExpanded] = useState(false);
   477→const [inputValue, setInputValue] = useState('');
   478→```
   479→
   480→### Global State (Zustand Stores)
   481→
   482→Use for app-wide data shared across widgets:
   483→
   484→```typescript
   485→import { useNotesStore } from '../../stores/useNotesStore';
   486→import { useKanbanStore } from '../../stores/useKanbanStore';
   487→import { useCalendarStore } from '../../stores/useCalendarStore';
   488→
   489→export const TaskSummaryWidget: React.FC = () => {
   490→  // Access global Kanban state
   491→  const tasks = useKanbanStore((state) => state.tasks);
   492→  const todoCount = tasks.filter(t => t.status === 'todo').length;
   493→
   494→  return (
   495→    <BaseWidget title="Task Summary" icon="✅">
   496→      <p>{todoCount} tasks remaining</p>
   497→    </BaseWidget>
   498→  );
   499→};
   500→```
   501→
   502→### Widget Settings (useWidgetStore)
   503→
   504→For widget-specific configuration (saved to IndexedDB):
   505→
   506→```typescript
   507→import { useWidgetStore } from '../../stores/useWidgetStore';
   508→
   509→export const WeatherWidget: React.FC = () => {
   510→  const widgetSettings = useWidgetStore((state) => state.widgetSettings);
   511→  const updateWidgetSettings = useWidgetStore((state) => state.updateWidgetSettings);
   512→
   513→  // Get widget-specific settings
   514→  const city = widgetSettings.weather?.city || 'New York';
   515→  const unit = widgetSettings.weather?.unit || 'fahrenheit';
   516→
   517→  // Update settings
   518→  const handleCityChange = (newCity: string) => {
   519→    updateWidgetSettings('weather', { city: newCity, unit });
   520→  };
   521→
   522→  // Use settings in API call
   523→  const fetchWeather = async () => {
   524→    const response = await fetch(`https://api.example.com/weather?city=${city}&unit=${unit}`);
   525→    // ...
   526→  };
   527→};
   528→```
   529→
   530→---
   531→
   532→## API Integration Best Practices
   533→
   534→### 1. Error Handling
   535→
   536→Always handle network errors gracefully:
   537→
   538→```typescript
   539→const fetchData = async () => {
   540→  setLoading(true);
   541→  setError(null);
   542→
   543→  try {
   544→    const response = await fetch('https://api.example.com/data');
   545→
   546→    // Check HTTP status
   547→    if (!response.ok) {
   548→      throw new Error(`HTTP ${response.status}: ${response.statusText}`);
   549→    }
   550→
   551→    const data = await response.json();
   552→
   553→    // Validate response structure
   554→    if (!data || !data.results) {
   555→      throw new Error('Invalid response format');
   556→    }
   557→
   558→    setData(data.results);
   559→  } catch (err) {
   560→    // User-friendly error messages
   561→    if (err instanceof TypeError && err.message.includes('Failed to fetch')) {
   562→      setError('Network error. Check your connection.');
   563→    } else {
   564→      setError(err instanceof Error ? err.message : 'Failed to load data');
   565→    }
   566→  } finally {
   567→    setLoading(false);
   568→  }
   569→};
   570→```
   571→
   572→### 2. CORS Handling
   573→
   574→Many APIs don't support CORS from browser. Options:
   575→
   576→**Option 1: Use CORS-friendly APIs** (preferred)
   577→- Open-Meteo (weather)
   578→- CoinGecko (crypto)
   579→- Hacker News API
   580→- Reddit JSON API
   581→
   582→**Option 2: User configures proxy**
   583→- Allow users to set custom CORS proxy in Settings
   584→- Never use central proxy (violates privacy model)
   585→
   586→**Example:**
   587→```typescript
   588→// Check if user has configured CORS proxy
   589→const corsProxy = useWidgetStore((state) => state.settings.corsProxy);
   590→const apiUrl = corsProxy
   591→  ? `${corsProxy}/https://api.example.com/data`
   592→  : 'https://api.example.com/data';
   593→```
   594→
   595→### 3. Rate Limiting
   596→
   597→Respect API rate limits:
   598→
   599→```typescript
   600→// Debounce user input
   601→import { debounce } from 'lodash';
   602→
   603→const debouncedSearch = debounce((query: string) => {
   604→  fetchSearchResults(query);
   605→}, 500); // Wait 500ms after user stops typing
   606→
   607→// Cache responses
   608→const [cache, setCache] = useState<Map<string, any>>(new Map());
   609→
   610→const fetchData = async (key: string) => {
   611→  // Check cache first
   612→  if (cache.has(key)) {
   613→    return cache.get(key);
   614→  }
   615→
   616→  const data = await fetch(`https://api.example.com?q=${key}`);
   617→  setCache(new Map(cache.set(key, data)));
   618→  return data;
   619→};
   620→
   621→// Limit refresh frequency
   622→const [lastRefresh, setLastRefresh] = useState(Date.now());
   623→
   624→const handleRefresh = () => {
   625→  const now = Date.now();
   626→  if (now - lastRefresh < 60000) { // 1 minute
   627→    setError('Please wait before refreshing again');
   628→    return;
   629→  }
   630→
   631→  setLastRefresh(now);
   632→  fetchData();
   633→};
   634→```
   635→
   636→### 4. Privacy-First API Usage
   637→
   638→**Preferred:** Static data (no API calls)
   639→- Local quote collections
   640→- Offline calculators
   641→- Client-side utilities
   642→
   643→**Acceptable:** Public APIs without authentication
   644→- Open-Meteo (weather)
   645→- Hacker News
   646→- CoinGecko
   647→
   648→**Requires user consent:** APIs with authentication
   649→- GitHub (requires username in settings)
   650→- API keys stored encrypted in IndexedDB
   651→
   652→**Example:**
   653→```typescript
   654→// Privacy-first: Static fallback data
   655→import { getRandomQuote } from '../../data/staticQuotes';
   656→
   657→const fetchQuote = async () => {
   658→  // Use static data (no API call, no tracking)
   659→  setQuote(getRandomQuote());
   660→};
   661→```
   662→
   663→---
   664→
   665→## Performance Optimization
   666→
   667→### 1. Lazy Loading
   668→
   669→Widgets with heavy dependencies should be lazy-loaded:
   670→
   671→```typescript
   672→// In Dashboard.tsx
   673→import { lazy, Suspense } from 'react';
   674→
   675→const WeatherMapWidget = lazy(() => import('./Dashboard/WeatherMapWidget'));
   676→
   677→// Render with Suspense
   678→<Suspense fallback={<LoadingSpinner />}>
   679→  <WeatherMapWidget />
   680→</Suspense>
   681→```
   682→
   683→### 2. Memoization
   684→
   685→Prevent unnecessary re-renders:
   686→
   687→```typescript
   688→import React, { useMemo, memo } from 'react';
   689→
   690→// Memoize expensive calculations
   691→const sortedTasks = useMemo(() => {
   692→  return tasks.sort((a, b) => a.priority - b.priority);
   693→}, [tasks]);
   694→
   695→// Memoize entire component if props rarely change
   696→export const TaskListWidget = memo(() => {
   697→  // Component implementation
   698→});
   699→```
   700→
   701→### 3. Virtualization
   702→
   703→For long lists (> 50 items), use virtualization:
   704→
   705→```typescript
   706→import { FixedSizeList as List } from 'react-window';
   707→
   708→<List
   709→  height={400}
   710→  itemCount={items.length}
   711→  itemSize={50}
   712→  width="100%"
   713→>
   714→  {({ index, style }) => (
   715→    <div style={style}>{items[index].title}</div>
   716→  )}
   717→</List>
   718→```
   719→
   720→---
   721→
   722→## Testing Checklist
   723→
   724→Before submitting a new widget:
   725→
   726→**Functionality:**
   727→- [ ] Widget renders without errors
   728→- [ ] Loading state displays correctly
   729→- [ ] Error handling works (test with network offline)
   730→- [ ] Refresh button updates data
   731→- [ ] Data persists across page refreshes (if using widget settings)
   732→
   733→**UI/UX:**
   734→- [ ] Widget works in light + dark mode
   735→- [ ] Text is readable (WCAG AA contrast)
   736→- [ ] Responsive design (test at different widget sizes)
   737→- [ ] Animations smooth (no jank)
   738→- [ ] Keyboard navigation works (Tab, Enter, ESC)
   739→
   740→**Performance:**
   741→- [ ] No excessive re-renders (check with React DevTools Profiler)
   742→- [ ] API calls debounced/throttled (if user input)
   743→- [ ] Bundle size impact < 50KB (check with `npm run build`)
   744→- [ ] Lazy loading used for heavy dependencies
   745→
   746→**Accessibility:**
   747→- [ ] Semantic HTML used (`<button>`, `<nav>`, `<article>`)
   748→- [ ] ARIA labels present
   749→- [ ] Focus states visible
   750→- [ ] Screen reader friendly (test with NVDA/JAWS)
   751→
   752→---
   753→
   754→## Widget Categories
   755→
   756→Choose the most appropriate category for your widget:
   757→
   758→**`core`** - Core app integrations (Notes, Calendar, Tasks)
   759→- Examples: Recent Notes, Upcoming Events
   760→- Always useful, enabled by default
   761→
   762→**`productivity`** - Productivity tools and utilities
   763→- Examples: Pomodoro Timer, World Clock, Currency Converter, Quote of the Day
   764→- Helps users work more efficiently
   765→
   766→**`news`** - News and information feeds
   767→- Examples: Hacker News, Reddit, Dev.to, Wikipedia
   768→- Keeps users informed
   769→
   770→**`finance`** - Financial data and tracking
   771→- Examples: Crypto Tracker, Stock Market
   772→- Displays market data
   773→
   774→**`fun`** - Games and entertainment
   775→- Examples: Memory Game, Typing Test, Developer Jokes
   776→- Provides breaks and entertainment
   777→
   778→**`visual`** - Visual and creative tools
   779→- Examples: Weather Map, Unsplash Photos
   780→- Emphasizes visual design
   781→
   782→**`dev`** - Developer tools and information
   783→- Examples: GitHub Trending, NPM Stats, Repo Stats
   784→- Developer-focused content
   785→
   786→**`utility`** - Utilities and tools
   787→- Examples: Calculator, QR Code Generator, Unit Converter, IP Info
   788→- General-purpose utilities
   789→
   790→---
   791→
   792→## Common Pitfalls & Solutions
   793→
   794→### Pitfall 1: CORS Errors
   795→
   796→**Problem:** API returns CORS error in browser console
   797→
   798→**Solution:**
   799→- Use CORS-friendly public APIs (Open-Meteo, Hacker News, Reddit JSON)
   800→- For APIs without CORS: Allow user to configure proxy in Settings
   801→- Never use central proxy (privacy violation)
   802→
   803→### Pitfall 2: Excessive Re-renders
   804→
   805→**Problem:** Widget re-renders on every parent state change
   806→
   807→**Solution:**
   808→```typescript
   809→// Use React.memo to prevent unnecessary re-renders
   810→export const MyWidget = memo(() => {
   811→  // Widget implementation
   812→});
   813→
   814→// Or useMemo for expensive calculations
   815→const processedData = useMemo(() => {
   816→  return data.map(item => expensiveTransform(item));
   817→}, [data]);
   818→```
   819→
   820→### Pitfall 3: API Rate Limits
   821→
   822→**Problem:** Too many API requests trigger rate limiting
   823→
   824→**Solution:**
   825→```typescript
   826→// Implement caching
   827→const [cache, setCache] = useState<Map<string, any>>(new Map());
   828→
   829→// Add cooldown to refresh button
   830→const [lastRefresh, setLastRefresh] = useState(0);
   831→const canRefresh = Date.now() - lastRefresh > 60000; // 1 minute cooldown
   832→```
   833→
   834→### Pitfall 4: Missing Dark Mode Support
   835→
   836→**Problem:** Widget looks broken in dark mode
   837→
   838→**Solution:**
   839→```typescript
   840→// Always use semantic color tokens with dark: variants
   841→<div className="bg-surface-light dark:bg-surface-dark">
   842→  <p className="text-text-light-primary dark:text-text-dark-primary">
   843→    Content
   844→  </p>
   845→</div>
   846→```
   847→
   848→### Pitfall 5: Bundle Size Bloat
   849→
   850→**Problem:** Widget adds 500KB+ to bundle
   851→
   852→**Solution:**
   853→```typescript
   854→// Lazy load heavy widgets
   855→const HeavyWidget = lazy(() => import('./HeavyWidget'));
   856→
   857→// Use lightweight alternatives
   858→// ❌ Moment.js (67KB)
   859→// ✅ date-fns (15KB)
   860→
   861→// ❌ Lodash (entire library 70KB)
   862→// ✅ Lodash (named imports, tree-shaken)
   863→import { debounce } from 'lodash';
   864→```
