## API Integration Best Practices

### 1. Error Handling

Always handle network errors gracefully:

```typescript
const fetchData = async () => {
  setLoading(true);
  setError(null);

  try {
    const response = await fetch('https://api.example.com/data');

    // Check HTTP status
    if (!response.ok) {
      throw new Error(`HTTP ${response.status}: ${response.statusText}`);
    }

    const data = await response.json();

    // Validate response structure
    if (!data || !data.results) {
      throw new Error('Invalid response format');
    }

    setData(data.results);
  } catch (err) {
    // User-friendly error messages
    if (err instanceof TypeError && err.message.includes('Failed to fetch')) {
      setError('Network error. Check your connection.');
    } else {
      setError(err instanceof Error ? err.message : 'Failed to load data');
    }
  } finally {
    setLoading(false);
  }
};
```

### 2. CORS Handling

Many APIs don't support CORS from browser. Options:

**Option 1: Use CORS-friendly APIs** (preferred)
- Open-Meteo (weather)
- CoinGecko (crypto)
- Hacker News API
- Reddit JSON API

**Option 2: User configures proxy**
- Allow users to set custom CORS proxy in Settings
- Never use central proxy (violates privacy model)

**Example:**
```typescript
// Check if user has configured CORS proxy
const corsProxy = useWidgetStore((state) => state.settings.corsProxy);
const apiUrl = corsProxy
  ? `${corsProxy}/https://api.example.com/data`
  : 'https://api.example.com/data';
```

### 3. Rate Limiting

Respect API rate limits:

```typescript
// Debounce user input
import { debounce } from 'lodash';

const debouncedSearch = debounce((query: string) => {
  fetchSearchResults(query);
}, 500); // Wait 500ms after user stops typing

// Cache responses
const [cache, setCache] = useState<Map<string, any>>(new Map());

const fetchData = async (key: string) => {
  // Check cache first
  if (cache.has(key)) {
    return cache.get(key);
  }

  const data = await fetch(`https://api.example.com?q=${key}`);
  setCache(new Map(cache.set(key, data)));
  return data;
};

// Limit refresh frequency
const [lastRefresh, setLastRefresh] = useState(Date.now());

const handleRefresh = () => {
  const now = Date.now();
  if (now - lastRefresh < 60000) { // 1 minute
    setError('Please wait before refreshing again');
    return;
  }

  setLastRefresh(now);
  fetchData();
};
```

### 4. Privacy-First API Usage

**Preferred:** Static data (no API calls)
- Local quote collections
- Offline calculators
- Client-side utilities

**Acceptable:** Public APIs without authentication
- Open-Meteo (weather)
- Hacker News
- CoinGecko

**Requires user consent:** APIs with authentication
- GitHub (requires username in settings)
- API keys stored encrypted in IndexedDB

**Example:**
```typescript
// Privacy-first: Static fallback data
import { getRandomQuote } from '../../data/staticQuotes';

const fetchQuote = async () => {
  // Use static data (no API call, no tracking)
  setQuote(getRandomQuote());
};
```

