## Performance Optimization

### 1. Lazy Loading

Widgets with heavy dependencies should be lazy-loaded:

```typescript
// In Dashboard.tsx
import { lazy, Suspense } from 'react';

const WeatherMapWidget = lazy(() => import('./Dashboard/WeatherMapWidget'));

// Render with Suspense
<Suspense fallback={<LoadingSpinner />}>
  <WeatherMapWidget />
</Suspense>
```

### 2. Memoization

Prevent unnecessary re-renders:

```typescript
import React, { useMemo, memo } from 'react';

// Memoize expensive calculations
const sortedTasks = useMemo(() => {
  return tasks.sort((a, b) => a.priority - b.priority);
}, [tasks]);

// Memoize entire component if props rarely change
export const TaskListWidget = memo(() => {
  // Component implementation
});
```

### 3. Virtualization

For long lists (> 50 items), use virtualization:

```typescript
import { FixedSizeList as List } from 'react-window';

<List
  height={400}
  itemCount={items.length}
  itemSize={50}
  width="100%"
>
  {({ index, style }) => (
    <div style={style}>{items[index].title}</div>
  )}
</List>
```

