## Common Pitfalls & Solutions

### Pitfall 1: CORS Errors

**Problem:** API returns CORS error in browser console

**Solution:**
- Use CORS-friendly public APIs (Open-Meteo, Hacker News, Reddit JSON)
- For APIs without CORS: Allow user to configure proxy in Settings
- Never use central proxy (privacy violation)

### Pitfall 2: Excessive Re-renders

**Problem:** Widget re-renders on every parent state change

**Solution:**
```typescript
// Use React.memo to prevent unnecessary re-renders
export const MyWidget = memo(() => {
  // Widget implementation
});

// Or useMemo for expensive calculations
const processedData = useMemo(() => {
  return data.map(item => expensiveTransform(item));
}, [data]);
```

### Pitfall 3: API Rate Limits

**Problem:** Too many API requests trigger rate limiting

**Solution:**
```typescript
// Implement caching
const [cache, setCache] = useState<Map<string, any>>(new Map());

// Add cooldown to refresh button
const [lastRefresh, setLastRefresh] = useState(0);
const canRefresh = Date.now() - lastRefresh > 60000; // 1 minute cooldown
```

### Pitfall 4: Missing Dark Mode Support

**Problem:** Widget looks broken in dark mode

**Solution:**
```typescript
// Always use semantic color tokens with dark: variants
<div className="bg-surface-light dark:bg-surface-dark">
  <p className="text-text-light-primary dark:text-text-dark-primary">
    Content
  </p>
</div>
```

### Pitfall 5: Bundle Size Bloat

**Problem:** Widget adds 500KB+ to bundle

**Solution:**
```typescript
// Lazy load heavy widgets
const HeavyWidget = lazy(() => import('./HeavyWidget'));

// Use lightweight alternatives
// ❌ Moment.js (67KB)
// ✅ date-fns (15KB)

// ❌ Lodash (entire library 70KB)
// ✅ Lodash (named imports, tree-shaken)
import { debounce } from 'lodash';
```

